UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.On Input Pressed.D: Broadcasts when the input is pressed.
Broadcasts when the input is released.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Unregister All Pla: Clears all players from the registered list. Registered players may be added or removed from the counted players depending on the Track Registered Players setting.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.StandardInput.Desc: Defines the input this device is listening for. These are the same binds that are used for the normal player actions. These actions shouldn't be used to determine player state, they're purely if the button bound to the action is held/released. In cases where these inputs don't exist on mobile, a custom button will be generated.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.CreativeInput.Desc: Defines the input this device is listening for. These binds can be changed for users in the 'Creative Input Actions' section. These may be rebound by users, so may not be the same keys as the standard actions. They will appear as separate buttons on mobile.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.RegisteredPlayerBe: Determines how players that are registered are counted by the device. ADD REGISTERED - Players can either be registered or counted by the device. REQUIRE REGISTERED- Players must be both registered and counted by the device. IGNORE REGISTERED - Players must be counted by the device but NOT registered.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Selected Class.Des: Determines which Class can activate the input.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Selected Team.Desc: Determines which team can activate the input.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Disable.Descriptio: Disables the device. When disabled, events won't be broadcast and any hud elements will not appear.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Enable.Description: Enables the Device. When Enabled, relevant players can press or release the input to broadcast the appropriate event.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Offset X.De: For mobile users, allow widget to be offset horizontally from its default placement.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Offset Y.De: For mobile users, allow widget to be offset vertically from its default placement.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Has Text.De: For mobile users, determines if the interaction icon shows the description text.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Color.Descr: For mobile users, determines the color of the interaction icon.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Icon.Descri: For mobile users, determines what icon to show on the Interaction Icon. If none, will use a hand icon.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Invert Class Selec: If set, the device will allow all but the selected class.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Invert Team Select: If set, the device will allow all but the selected team.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.CanActivateWhileSp: If true spectating players will be able to activate this input.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Axis Direction.Des: If your input is an axis, this determines which direction to listen for. Negative is left or backwards, positive is right or forwards.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Register Player.De: Registers the instigating player. Registered players may be added or removed from the counted players depending on the Track Registered Players setting.
Removes the instigating player from the registered list. Registered players may be added or removed from the counted players depending on the Track Registered Players setting.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Enabled at Game St: Should we track this input for all applicable players at game start
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Input Type.Descrip: Tracks either a standard input or a custom input. Standard inputs are used by other actions, and this device listens for the buttons bound to those actions being pressed/released. Creative Input Actions are custom actions only used by the Input Trigger.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Mobile Use Direct: When set to On, allow direct screen offsets for Input Trigger mobile button placement.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.HUD Description.De: When shown on HUD, determines what text to show. Use {input} to show the current input.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Show On HUD.Descri: Whether to show this input to players on the HUD.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_InputTrigger_C.Consume Input.Desc: Will stop the input from being read by other actions using the same button/key.
